data.chText: 例子；事例；实例
data.enText: a particular example or case of sth

data.chText: 这篇报道重点列举了一些不公正的实例。
data.enText: The report highlights a number of instances of injustice.

data.chText: 多数情况下，不必继续治疗。
data.enText: In most instances, there will be no need for further treatment.

data.chText: 我通常会建议休假，但就这个情况而言，我不敢保证休假会有什么好处。
data.enText: I would normally suggest taking time off work, but in this instance I'm not sure that would do any good.
for instance

data.chText: 例如；比如
data.enText: for example

data.chText: 比如说，如果你发现有职员偷东西，你会怎么办？
data.enText: What would you do, for instance, if you found a member of staff stealing?
in the first instance

data.chText: 第一；首先
data.enText: as the first part of a series of actions

data.chText: 首先是报警，然后与你的保险公司联系。
data.enText: In the first instance, notify the police and then contact your insurance company.

data.chText: 举…为例
data.enText: to give sth as an example

data.chText: 以上各词均指事例、实例、例证。
data.enText: These are all words for a thing or situation that is typical of a particular group or set, and is sometimes used to support an argument.
example

data.chText: 指实例、例证、典型、范例、样品：
data.enText: something such as an object, a fact or a situation that shows, explains or supports what you say; a thing that is typical of or represents a particular group or set

data.chText: 你能给我举个实例来解释你的意思吗？
data.enText: Can you give me an example of what you mean?
case

data.chText: 指具体情况、事例、实例、特定情况：
data.enText: a particular situation or a situation of a particular type; a situation that relates to a particular person or thing

data.chText: 在某些情况下，必须等上好几周才能得到约见。
data.enText: In some cases people have had to wait several weeks for an appointment.
instance

data.chText: 指例子、事例、实例：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) a particular situation or a situation of a particular type

data.chText: 这篇报道重点列举了一些不公正的实例。
data.enText: The report highlights a number of instances of injustice.
specimen

data.chText: 尤指动植物的物种：
data.enText: an example of sth, especially an animal or plant

data.chText: 水族馆里有一些很有趣的罕见的热带鱼。
data.enText: The aquarium has some interesting specimens of unusual tropical fish.
illustration

data.chText: 指说明事实的故事、实例、事例：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) a story, an event or an example that clearly shows the truth about sth

data.chText: 这组统计数字清楚地阐明了我要陈述的观点。
data.enText: The statistics are a clear illustration of the point I am trying to make.

data.chText: 用example还是illustration？
illustration常用以表示事物的真实性，example用以解释说明。
data.enText: An illustration is often used to show that sth is true. An example is used to help to explain sth.
example or illustration?
a(n) example/case/instance/specimen/illustration of sth
in a particular case/instance
for example/instance

ex.chText: 他的报告重点列举了一些歧视的事例。
ex.enText: His report highlights some instances of discrimination.

ex.chText: 在这一点上她承认他被冤枉了。
ex.enText: In this instance she admitted that he was wronged.

synonyms.bx: 指某个特定情况的例子。

ex.chText: 你能不能给我举个定语从句的例子呢？
ex.enText: Would you please give me an example of an attributive clause?

ex.chText: 这栋大楼是欧洲建筑风格的范例。
ex.enText: This building is a good example of European architecture.

synonyms.bx: 指用来解释、支持某一概括性观点或代表某个群体特点的具体的人、事物等。

ex.chText: 护士取了一份血样去化验。
ex.enText: The nurse took a blood sample for tests.

ex.chText: 他们想看看他的产品的一些样品。
ex.enText: They wanted to see some samples of his products.

synonyms.bx: 指从某一群体中选取出来的一部分人或事物，以供检验并发现有关该群体的信息。

ex.chText: 他的血样已经被送到了医院。
ex.enText: His blood specimen has been sent to the hospital.

ex.chText: 在过去几年里，他收集了几百种岩石标本。
ex.enText: He has collected hundreds of rock specimens in the past few years.

synonyms.bx: 指用于医学化验的血液、尿液或其他体液样本，或其他用于测试、检验的样品，也可指供学习、研究等用的动物、植物、矿物等的实例。

data.enText: for example

data.chText: 比如说，如果你发现有职员偷东西，你会怎么办？

tr: an item of information that is typical of a class or group
example: this patient provides a typical example of the syndrome
there is an example on page 10
it was a case of bad judgment
but there is always the famous example of the Smiths

tr: clarify by giving an example of

value.def: You use for instance to introduce a particular event, situation, or person that is an example of what you are talking about.

example.ex: There are a number of improvements; for instance, both mouse buttons can now be used...
example.tran: 在许多地方有了改进,例如,鼠标的左右键都可以使用了。

example.ex: Let your child make some of the small decisions concerning his daily routine. For instance, allow him to choose what clothes he wears at the weekend.
example.tran: 让孩子在日常生活中作一些小决定。比如,让他自己决定周末穿什么衣服。

value.def: An instance is a particular example or occurrence of something.

example.ex: She cited an instance where their training had been a marvelous help in dealing with problems.
example.tran: 她举了一个所受训练为解决问题帮了大忙的实例。

example.ex: ...an investigation into a serious instance of corruption.
example.tran: 对一起严重的腐败事件的调查

value.def: You say in the first instance to mention something that is the first step in a series of actions.

example.ex: In the first instance your child will be seen by an ear, nose and throat specialist...
example.tran: 你的孩子将首先由耳鼻喉专科医生来诊察。

example.ex: The post was for one year in the first instance with possible renewal to a further year.
example.tran: 该岗位初始为一年期,有可能会再续聘一年。

value.def: If you do something at someone's instance, you do it because they have ordered or requested you to do it.

example.ex: The rally was organised at the instance of two senior cabinet ministers.
example.tran: 集会是应两位资深内阁大臣的要求组织的。
